  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The context of use narrative explicitly requires that predicted hemolysis indices remain below a normalised threshold of NIH < 0.005 g/100 L under all simulated operating conditions — a patient-safety constraint tied to clinical transfusion risk. This threshold obligation is not captured in the linked requirement set.",
